				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Little Mouse" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;quot;Little Mouse&amp;quot; is a children's sequencing game which uses the imagery and phrasing from the book, &amp;quot;The Little Mouse, the Red Ripe Strawberry, and the Big Hungry Bear&amp;quot; by Audrey and Don Wood.  The game contains 48 thick cards with 4 each of the 12 different phrases to play any of six different games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;[paraphrased rules]&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1. Solo Sequencing&amp;#10;Solitary sequencing in which one set of 12 different cards are laid face-up.  The player places the cards in sequence according to the original story.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. Scramble Sequencing&amp;#10;For 2-4 players.  All 48 cards are placed face-up.  The first player to complete a sequence wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3. Skill Sequencing&amp;#10;For 2-4 players. Cards are shuffled.  The top four cards are laid face-up, the rest are dealt to the players.  Each turn, the player places a card before or after one of the four middle cards.  First player to use all cards wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4. Quartet&amp;#10;For 2-4 players.  Players seek to obtain all four of a particular card.  Player with the highest number of sets wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;5. Snap&amp;#10;For 2-4 players.  Traditional Snap game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;6. Matching Words to Pictures&amp;#10;For 2-4 players. A single storyline set is dealt to each player.  A leader displays either picture or word card and the other players have to match its opposite (words-to-picture or picture-to-words)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
